obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_1740  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 30/10/2017 Pim\n- Data in Fig.4 shows PCDH17-Mediated Intercellular Homophilic Interaction and Fig.S5, 6, S6, 7 show effects on synapse development. I would propose to create one BP ticket based on this paper against 'synapse adhesion between pre- and post-synapse (GO:0099560)'. I do not see what stage of synapse development is affected, so I do not annotate this more specifically.\n\nFig.4: PCDH17-Mediated Intercellular Homophilic Interaction. Experiments show direct interaction of PCDH17 in trans (HEK cells) and co-localization with PCDH17 in co-cultured neurons. The adhesion term is derived from the know role of cadherins in cell adhesion.. Experimental description: Paper focussed on mouse brain lysate, brain section, slices and whole animal as indicated in the Figure legends (e.g. Figure 1 B \"mouse brain lysate\" and supplementary figures (e.g. Supplementary Figure 1 .\"...in serial coronal sections of a P10 mouse\") Primate brain section staining described in figure 8 but not used in the annotation.\n\n30/10/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed recombinant protein in pull FC-puldown essays is human species: \"To generate the PCDH17E-Fc fusion protein, the clone of human IgG1 Fc region was raised from standard RT-PCR and its cDNA\"\n- CHO cells express mouse Protocadherin-17\n- Mouse species was selected based on KO data and species of overexpressed protein." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1740" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

